{"id": 2058, "title": "Ticket #2058: Debian native packaging for Condor", "description": "<blockquote>\nThis ticket serves as umbrella ticket for the native debian packaging work for Condor. Most of this work is/has been done by Michael Hanke and is to be integrated/reviewed by the Condor team. Every ticket relating to this effort should be derived from here.\n\n<p><span class=\"wiki\"><a href=\"wiki?p=DebianPackagingMeetingNotes\" title=\"Debian Packaging Meeting Notes\">DebianPackagingMeetingNotes</a></span></p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2011-May-12 15:05:26 by tannenba:</em> <br/>\n\nFor first step, by end of May we want to\n<ol>\n<li>get a written plan from Tim (derived from discussions at Condor Week)\n</li><li>create a git branch to hold all below patches, with commit access to this branch for Michael\n</li><li>merge many of the 'no-brainer' patches to the master branch for inclusion into v7.7.\n</li></ol>\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2011-May-19 16:23:00 by cweiss:</em> <br/>\n\nAll changes related to this go into branch V7_7-debian-publicbranch .. since they seem to be reasonably interesting to various people\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2012-Mar-08 01:34:13 by mih:</em> <br/>\n\nJust saw this ticket being listed as \"stalled\" -- it is actually quite the opposite. A first upload of Condor 7.7.4 to Debian experimental has happened -- and it was accepted. That means Condor is now an official Debian package, hence the major goal is achieved. What remains to do is to iron out a few more things (see related tickets), make an upload to Debian unstable and ensure its transition into Debian testing.\n\n<p>Condor source package in Debian experimental:\n\n</p><p></p><pre>  http://packages.debian.org/source/experimental/condor\n</pre>\n\n<p>Condor in the Debian BTS:\n\n</p><p></p><pre>  http://bugs.debian.org/src:condor</pre>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" 